Inside, attendees utilize tablets at kiosks to upload their information and assess recruiter enthusiasm while small groups rehearse elevator pitches with career counselors. A whiteboard lists employers offering same-day interviews, and as the event progresses toward its final hour, monitors display a post-event survey link, accompanied by the aroma of coffee and catered snacks, while students exit carrying tote bags and stacks of business cards.

Inside, students assess recruiters' enthusiasm, compare various swag items, and rehearse elevator pitches, while a whiteboard lists employers conducting same-day interviews. Career counselors assist students with industry guidance and visa sponsorship information. Cameras capture interviews as the event progresses, and an alumni panel discusses technical interview preparation, culminating in an announcement signaling the final hour, with students exiting carrying tote bags and stacks of business cards.

Career counselors remind attendees to maintain eye contact during interactions, and staff at the entrance scan registrations and hand out lanyards. Near the stage, the engineering society sponsors a resume review table, and a data science company showcases a live dashboard of fair attendance. A cybersecurity company runs a password cracking challenge on a laptop, and consulting firms present glossy case study booklets. Small groups discuss enthusiastic recruiters and analyze them, while human resources jot notes on tablets. As the day progresses, interview sign-up sheets fill, and students exit with tote bags filled with notebooks and pens, alongside a stack of business cards. A post-event survey link flashes on monitors near the exit, and recruiters encourage personalized email follow-ups.

Healthcare providers exhibit photos from their community outreach initiatives, while consulting firms stack glossy case study booklets on high tables. Recruiters distribute tote bags filled with branded notebooks and pens, as students analyze which recruiters seem most enthusiastic and compare swag items like water bottles and phone chargers. Small groups rehearse elevator pitches quietly against the wall, and career counselors guide students on eye contact while redirecting unsure individuals to appropriate industries. The aroma of coffee and catered snacks fills the venue, with a whiteboard listing employers scheduling same-day interviews.
